if you don’t know how to say an activity in Chinese.
Read the schedule below, which shows what a Chinese student’s schedule for Friday
and Saturday might look like. (Students in China all have different schedules!) The
asterisks show things that the student is required to do.
Be prepared to answer the following questions in class.
How is your schedule and this Chinese student’s schedule the same? Do you both
need to do some of the same things?
Are there things you have to do that this student does not, or things this student
has to do that you do not?
Who is busier, you or the Chinese student?
